<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-078-426  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 078 426.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Jan 15 1990 n283 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>'David and Goliath' fight. (Stonehouse andamp; Co sues IBM )andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Stonehouse andamp; Co filed a law suit charging IBM with strong-armingMCI Communications Corp into backing out of an oral agreement.andO;Stonehouse contends MCI agreed to use their Monies networkmanagement system in a bid for a voice and data system for ChevronIndustries Inc. IBM told MCI it preferred its own networkmanagement products over Monies and threatened to withdraw fromMCI's bidding team if MCI did not comply.andP;  MCI would not be ableto meet the specifications of the request for proposals if IBMwithdrew.andP;  Stonehouse alleges a breach of a confidentialrelationship, breach of duty in good faith and fair dealing, andinterference with a contractual relationship.andP;  They are seeking aninjunction preventing IBM from engaging in this type of practice,as well as unspecified damages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (cases)Stonehouse and Co. (cases).andO;Ticker:    IBM; MCI.andO;Topic:     Law SuitContractsRequest for ProposalsNetwork Management Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>